### Incrond Summary
Incron uses the [[kernel]] [[inotify]] capability to watch for file changes, and executes a command when a match in the incrontab file is made.

### Incrontab
I prefer to use incrontab files in /etc/incron.d/. Here's an example:
<pre>

/var/www/virtual/www.yodnsconf.com/public/web/2008/08    IN_CLOSE_WRITE    /usr/local/bin/synchronize_this.sh    /var/www/virtual/www.yodnsconf.com/public/web/2008/08
</pre>